AB  - In 1983, the public was given its first opportunity to review bank asset quality in the form of non-performaing asset information. The purpose of this study is to evaluate that information. A regression analysis comparing the non-performing asset statistics with examiner classifications of assets suggests that the non-performing asset information can be useful aid in analyzing the asset quality of banks, particularly when the information is timely.
